<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- M1 (pickup): single chord E2-B2-E3 LH, G#4 B4 RH — sparse start
- M2 (E F#m): 4-note E open bass E2-B2-E3-G#3; F#m F#2-C#3-A3
- M3 (B E): ⑤ B full 4-note B2-F#3-B3-D#4; ① E 3-note E3-B3-E4
- M4 (F#m7 A): ②7 rich bass F#2-C#3-E3-A3; ④ A A2-E3-A3-C#4
- M5 (F#m E): compact motion between ② and ①
- M8 (C#m): ⑥ "333" G#4-B4-E5 three-note RH — first "333" in arrangement
- M10: ①¹ first inversion (verse 2 variety) B4-E5; LH E2-B2-G#3-E3
- M16: ⑥ C#m "333" G#4-C#5-E5 — richer ⑥ in second verse
- M19: ④ A reaches A5 in RH (highest pitch) — climax at "thy boundless love" text
- M20: ①"33" G#4-B4-E5 full; ⑥ C#m passing
- M22: ① "33" G#4-B4-E5 + ⑤ B full bass B2-F#3-B3-D#4
- M23: ④→⑥→② descending bass A→C#→F# — three-chord walkdown
- M24: ①①¹ then ②7 F#m7 — leading into final cadence
- M25: ① "334" G#4-B4-E5-G#5 full 4-note close, E1 pedal

VOICE LEADING:
- M2→3: F#m→B: C#3 common tone LH
- M4→5: A→F#m: A3 common tone
- M8: G#4 sustained in RH through ⑥→① transition
- M19: ④ A5 climax — highest note of arrangement
- M23: chromatic descending bass A→C#→F# = falling third sequence

TEXTURE ARC:
- M1-8: Verse 1 — spare and hymn-like, 2-note RH opening
- M9-16: Verse 2 — same harmony, richer inversions (①¹, ⑥"333")
- M17-22: Bridge — ③m G#m color (M17), ⑥ C#m/① dance (M20)
- M19: Climax — ④ A5 RH peak
- M23-25: Final cadence — three-chord walkdown, ①"334" close with E1
-->
